solution.p:
We can rationalize the denominator by multiplying mumerator and denominator by \blert{\sqrt{3}}:
	\dfrac{3\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{3}} \cdot \blert{\dfrac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}}} = \dfrac{3\sqrt{6}}{3} = \sqrt{6}
or we can divide 3 by \sqrt{3} to get \sqrt{3}.  (Remember that \sqrt{3}~\sqrt{3} = 3.)
	\dfrac{\blert{3}\sqrt{2}}{\blert{\sqrt{3}}} = \blert{\sqrt{3}}~\sqrt{2} = \sqrt{6}

The LCD for the two fractions is 2, and the building factor for the first fraction is \blert{\sqrt{2}}.
	\dfrac{3}{\sqrt{2}} + \dfrac{5}{2} \amp = \dfrac{3}{\sqrt{2}} \cdot \blert{\dfrac{\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2}}} + \dfrac{5}{2}
		 \amp = \dfrac{3\sqrt{2}}{2} + \dfrac{5}{2} = \dfrac{3\sqrt{2}+5}{2}

statement.p:
Write each expression without negative exponents.

\dfrac{1}{4}xy^{-2}

a^{-3}b^{-2}

\dfrac{2a^{-1}}{4}{bc}^{-2}}

\dfrac{x}{y^{-2}}+\dfrac{x^{-2}}{y}

solution.p:
We use the fact that  ~a^{-n} = \dfrac{1}{a^n}, and consequently that ~\dfrac{1}{a^{-n}} = a^n.


\dfrac{x}{4y^2}

\dfrac{1}{a^{3}b^{2}}

\dfrac{2c^2}{ab}

xy^{2}}+\dfrac{1}{x^2y}

